 (genitive <i>Wulfes</i>) + <i>tūn</i>. The Essex placename derives from the Old English personal name <i>Wulfhelm</i> (genitive <i>Wulfhelmes</i>) + <i>tūn</i>. There may have been some confusion with   Wollaston  ."]}]},{"name":"Ethelreda","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized form of the Old English female personal name <i>Æðelþryð</i> (  see  Audrey  ). It was taken up as a given name in the 19th‐century, but is now very rare."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Ethelreda Wolston was born in 1466, in Huntingdon, Huntingdonshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Sir Guy Wolston, was 34 and her mother, Margaret De Huntingdon, was 33. She married Sir Thomas Empson in 1486, in London, Middlesex, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1466–":"1466–Surnud","1462–1548":"1462–1548","1463–1508":"1463–1508","1466–Female":"1466–Surnud","1466–1490":"1466–1490","1490–1545":"1490–1545","1433–1490":"1433–1490","1433–1503":"1433–1503","1503":"1503","1545":"1545","1466":"1466","1433":"1433","1486":"1486","1463":"1463","1462":"1462","1508":"1508","1490":"1490","1548":"1548","City of Westminster, London, Greater London, England, United Kingdom":"London, Middlesex, England","Huntingdon, Huntingdonshire, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Huntingdon, Huntingdonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Westminster, Middlesex, England, United Kingdom":"Westminster, Middlesex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1466–":"1466–Kuollut","1462–1548":"1462–1548","1463–1508":"1463–1508","1466–Female":"1466–Kuollut","1466–1490":"1466–1490","1490–1545":"1490–1545","1433–1490":"1433–1490","1433–1503":"1433–1503","1503":"1503","1545":"1545","1466":"1466","1433":"1433","1486":"1486","1463":"1463","1462":"1462","1508":"1508","1490":"1490","1548":"1548","City of Westminster, London, Greater L